1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:09,350
(John 12:25): I quote in Latin the gospel saying of our Lord, ‘He that hateth his soul in this world shall keep it in eternal life.

2
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:14,025
Now mark what it is our Lord means when he speaks of a man hating his soul.

3
00:00:14,025 --> 00:00:23,925
He that loveth his soul in this mortal life and as she exists in this world shall lose her in eternal life; but he that hateth her mortal guise shall keep her unto life eternal.

4
00:00:23,925 --> 00:00:27,375
There are two reasons for his using here the word soul.

5
00:00:27,375 --> 00:00:35,237
According to one authority soul is a name for the ground (or soil) and has nothing to do with the nature (or ground) of the soul.

6
00:00:35,237 --> 00:00:42,012
As a master has said, Whoso discourses of moveable things trenches not on the nature or ground of the soul.

7
00:00:42,012 --> 00:00:48,737
Try to name the soul as she is in herself, in her pure and abstract nature, and not a name can we find.

8
00:00:48,737 --> 00:00:55,537
They call her soul as they call a carpenter, neither a human being nor after any being at all but after his work.

9
00:00:55,537 --> 00:01:04,775
What our Lord means is this: he that loveth his soul in her nakedness, her impartible soul-nature, to wit, will hate and despise her in this dress.

10
00:01:04,775 --> 00:01:10,000
She hates and detests and rues being so far from the pure light she is in herself.

11
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:16,550
Our doctors say the soul is called fire because of the force and because of the heat and because of the light that is in her.

12
00:01:16,550 --> 00:01:20,112
Others declare she is a spark of the celestial nature.

13
00:01:20,112 --> 00:01:22,450
A third school calls her a light.

14
00:01:22,450 --> 00:01:24,437
A fourth calls her a breath.

15
00:01:24,437 --> 00:01:26,437
A fifth dubs her a number.

16
00:01:26,437 --> 00:01:30,512
They are trying to describe the soul by something pure and luminous.

17
00:01:30,512 --> 00:01:39,712
Number exists in the angels and in light there is number as well, but to name her after the highest and after the brightest is still to fall short of the ground of the soul.

18
00:01:39,712 --> 00:01:45,612
God who is nameless is ineffable and in her ground the soul too is ineffable as he is ineffable.

19
00:01:45,612 --> 00:01:48,837
There is another reason for his saying that she hates.

20
00:01:48,837 --> 00:02:00,037
This term we apply to the soul is the name of the soul as she is in the prison of the body, so he means the soul in her individual state, still at the stage of taking thought, still in her prison-house.

21
00:02:00,037 --> 00:02:08,825
By taking thought for these nether things, by taking them in by her senses at all, she is confined: words cannot name any higher nature within her.

22
00:02:08,956 --> 00:02:12,406
There are three reasons why my soul should hate herself.

23
00:02:12,356 --> 00:02:16,531
The first, that in so far as she is mine she is not God’s.

24
00:02:16,531 --> 00:02:21,981
The second, because my soul is not wholly imbedded and set and re-cast into God.

25
00:02:21,981 --> 00:02:26,918
Augustine says, To have God for one’s own one must needs first be God’s.

26
00:02:26,918 --> 00:02:33,418
The third reason is: the soul’s enjoying herself as the soul while enjoying God with the soul, which is wrong.

27
00:02:33,418 --> 00:02:37,481
She should be enjoying God in herself since he is entirely hers.

28
00:02:37,481 --> 00:02:41,293
As Christ says, ‘he that loveth his soul shall lose it.

29
00:02:41,293 --> 00:02:48,193
What the soul is in this world or beholds in this world: things comprehended, apparent at all, she shall hate.

30
00:02:48,193 --> 00:02:56,106
A master declares that the soul at her highest and purest transcends the whole world, nothing attaching the soul to the world but affection.

31
00:02:56,106 --> 00:02:59,056
Sometimes she has a natural love of the body.

32
00:02:59,056 --> 00:03:02,556
Sometimes she has a will inclined towards creatures.

33
00:03:02,556 --> 00:03:10,168
Another says the soul has no natural concern with the things of this world any more than the ear has with colour or the eye has with song.

34
00:03:10,168 --> 00:03:15,818
Our natural philosophers teach that the body is much rather in the soul than the soul is in the body.

35
00:03:15,818 --> 00:03:23,406
Even as the cask contains the wine and not the wine the cask, so does the soul keep the body in her rather than the body the soul.

36
00:03:23,406 --> 00:03:27,231
What the soul loves in this world she is pure from by nature.

37
00:03:27,231 --> 00:03:36,681
According to one philosopher, it is the soul’s nature and her natural end to achieve within herself a feat of understanding, God informing her with the general idea.

38
00:03:36,681 --> 00:03:45,756
He that can say he has attained his nature finds all things within himself, fashioned in light as they are in God; not as they are in nature but as they are in God.

39
00:03:45,756 --> 00:03:50,093
Neither spirit nor angel touches the ground or nature of the soul.

40
00:03:50,093 --> 00:03:56,506
In it she comes into the first, into the beginning, whence God breaks out in goodness into all creatures.

41
00:03:56,506 --> 00:04:04,018
There she loves all things in God, not pure as they are in her uncompounded nature, but merely impartible as they are in God.

42
00:04:04,018 --> 00:04:07,343
God has made this whole world as it were out of coal.

43
00:04:07,343 --> 00:04:11,106
Its pattern in gold is more lasting than this one in coal.

44
00:04:11,106 --> 00:04:15,993
Likewise the things in the soul are purer and nobler than they are in this world.

45
00:04:15,993 --> 00:04:22,456
The material which God made things out of is (to its exemplar in God) baser than coal is to gold.

46
00:04:22,456 --> 00:04:28,131
For the purpose of making a crock a man takes a handful of clay; that is the medium he works in.

47
00:04:28,131 --> 00:04:32,231
He gives it a form he has in him, nobler than his material.

48
00:04:32,231 --> 00:04:44,556
And the moral of this is that the things in the intelligible world, the soul, to wit, are infinitely nobler than they are in this; even as the image hewn and graven in gold so the types of all things are enfolded in the soul.

49
00:04:44,556 --> 00:04:50,143
A master says, The soul has a natural gift for being impressed with the forms of all things.

50
00:04:50,143 --> 00:04:59,731
Another one says, Never did soul get to her virgin nature without finding all things imaged therein in the intelligible world which is incomprehensible, unthinkable.

51
00:04:59,731 --> 00:05:04,693
Gregory says: All reasoning in words about divine things is but a stammering.

52
00:05:04,852 --> 00:05:07,889
One word more about the soul and I have done.

53
00:05:07,839 --> 00:05:12,139
O ye daughters of Jerusalem, look not upon me because I am brown!

54
00:05:12,139 --> 00:05:17,102
The sun hath coloured me and the children of my mother have striven against me’ (Cant.

55
00:05:17,102 --> 00:05:22,014
I). She refers to the children of this world, to them the soul speaks.

56
00:05:22,014 --> 00:05:28,552
The sun is the lust of this world: the visible, tangible things thereof do turn me swarthy and brown.

57
00:05:28,552 --> 00:05:32,789
Brown is not a pure colour: it is part light and part darkness.

58
00:05:32,789 --> 00:05:39,114
When the soul thinks or acts with her powers how enlightened soever these be, still, there is confusion.

59
00:05:39,114 --> 00:05:43,339
And therefore she says, ‘My mother’s children have striven against me.

60
00:05:43,339 --> 00:05:48,427
These children being the lower powers of the soul, all clashing and at strife with her.

61
00:05:48,427 --> 00:05:52,427
The heavenly Father is our father and christendom is our mother.

62
00:05:52,427 --> 00:05:57,627
What though she be fair and well-favoured and good at her work, yet this is not perfect.

63
00:05:57,627 --> 00:06:02,327
Wherefore he cries, ‘O thou fairest among women go forth and depart.

64
00:06:02,327 --> 00:06:05,014
This world is like a woman, weak.

65
00:06:05,014 --> 00:06:08,489
But why does he address her, ‘O fairest among women’?

66
00:06:08,489 --> 00:06:11,577
The angels are fair and are far above the soul.

67
00:06:11,577 --> 00:06:14,889
He says, ‘fairest’: in her light-nature.

68
00:06:14,889 --> 00:06:21,402
Go forth and depart’: go forth from this world and depart from such things as thy soul is still prone to.

69
00:06:21,402 --> 00:06:23,902
And anything grasped let her hate.
